        "canonical_link": null,
        "text": "Registry hack required, excellent support though : Hor+ gameplay & real-time cut scenes, unstretched/pillarboxed intro videos, unstretched centered HUD...\n\nMouse sensitivity seems tied to the display width, so even at 10 it feels a bit low. Fortunately you can edit that in the registry too, and set it beyond the in-game max. Setting the Mouse value to 20 in the registry works great in 5040.\n\nGo to start run type REGEDIT click open in your registry go to local machine/SOFTWARE/VUGAMES/Scarface then on the right hand side there is two keys one says Screenheight/Screenwidth just type in what ever resolution you need there ... and you can still make changes in the games video menu like AA/AF etc and it will hold you resolution Enjoy\n\nNote: You must change the resolution at least once in the game to get the keys to appear in the registry ... and in the game it will not show the resolution you have chosen.\n\nIt works great ... the HUD stays on the centre screen ..."
